  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "GPT-4 achieved comparable (or superior) performance with human annotators in five of the six datasets where inter-annotator agreement was available.",
    "Additionally, the fact that LLM-generated norms could be substituted for human norms in a statistical model without changing the sign of any coefficients in the model suggests that these norms could be used to help drive theoretical inferences about how psycholinguistic variables relate to one another.",
    "Further, GPT-4 was presented with instructions that were identical (or nearly identical) to those presented to human participants.",
    "Thus, these results may reflect a lower-bound on GPT-4's ability to produce aligned judgments.",
    "Better results could be obtained with alternative prompting methods (Reynolds & McDonell, 2021), well-chosen examples (Brown et al., 2020), or other ways of extracting LLM output (Hu & Levy, 2023)."
  ],
